kmod-amneziawg: pass crypto-lib/udptunnel symvers explicitly

On the openwrt-nss-edma fork, $(KERNEL_MAKE_FLAGS) only sets
KBUILD_EXTRA_SYMBOLS to a fixed NSS-oriented set
(gpio-button-hotplug, qca-mcs, qca-ppe-nss) rather than deriving it
from this package's own DEPENDS. amneziawg.ko therefore links against
kmod-udptunnel4/6 and kmod-crypto-lib-chacha20poly1305/curve25519
(all four already built as declared DEPENDS) but modpost cannot see
their exported symbols, and fails with:

  ERROR: modpost: "chacha20poly1305_encrypt_sg_inplace" [amneziawg.ko] undefined!
  ERROR: modpost: "curve25519" [amneziawg.ko] undefined!
  ...

The four symvers files exist under $(LINUX_DIR)/symvers/ once their
kmod packages are built (same directory/naming convention observed
for the three NSS ones above) - list them explicitly instead of
relying on the fork's fixed set. Keep the original three so nothing
that did rely on them regresses.

--- a/kmod-amneziawg/Makefile
+++ b/kmod-amneziawg/Makefile
@@ -39,6 +39,13 @@
 		M="$(PKG_BUILD_DIR)/$(MAKE_PATH)" \
 		EXTRA_CFLAGS="$(BUILDFLAGS)" \
 		WIREGUARD_VERSION="$(WIREGUARD_VERSION)" \
+		KBUILD_EXTRA_SYMBOLS="$(LINUX_DIR)/symvers/gpio-button-hotplug.symvers \
+			$(LINUX_DIR)/symvers/qca-mcs.symvers \
+			$(LINUX_DIR)/symvers/qca-ppe-nss.symvers \
+			$(LINUX_DIR)/symvers/udptunnel4.symvers \
+			$(LINUX_DIR)/symvers/udptunnel6.symvers \
+			$(LINUX_DIR)/symvers/crypto-lib-chacha20poly1305.symvers \
+			$(LINUX_DIR)/symvers/crypto-lib-curve25519.symvers" \
 		modules
 endef
